    <para id="para-00026">At the <term class="no-emphasis" id="term-00038">Battle of Zama</term> in 202 BCE, the Roman army defeated Hannibal, and the Roman commander <term class="no-emphasis" id="term-00039">Scipio</term> earned the nickname “Africanus” (<link target-id="fig-00005"/>). Carthage sued for peace and was stripped of all its overseas territory. Rome thus acquired Carthage’s lands in Hispania.</para>
